parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 1st Person Singular
str2: (a) I say, speak; I mean, mention, tell, (b) I call, name, especially in the pass., (c) I tell, command.
From a primary nemo; law, genitive case, specially, (including the volume); also of the Gospel), or figuratively.

parse: Verb - Perfect Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: A prolongation and middle voice form of a primary verb; to cause to be, i.e. to become, used with great latitude.
Four hundred. Plural from tessares and hekaton; four hundred.
A year. Apparently a primary word; a year.
(a) gen: with, in company with, (b) acc: (1) behind, beyond, after, of place, (2) after, of time, with nouns, neut. of adjectives.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To annul, make of no effect, cancel. To invalidate.
From diatithemai; properly, a disposition, i.e. a contract.

parse: Verb - Perfect Participle Middle or Passive - Accusative Feminine Singular
str2: To establish or ratify before. From pro and kuroo; to ratify previously.
A primary preposition; under, i.e. of place, or with verbs; of place (underneath) or where (below) or time (when).
A deity, especially the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; by Hebraism, very.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
From kata and argeo; to be entirely idle, literally or figuratively.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A promise. From epaggello; an announcement.
